TESTING INFORMATION 

OVERVIEW
    We use CMake/CTest and QEMU to run tests for ARM32 and AArch64. Though I imagine AArch64 tests 
    will primarily be restricted to lens and soul for the foreseeable. 

STRUCTURE
    tests/
        CMakeLists.txt  - Test registration and build rules
    tests/<component>/
        *.sh            - Generic & arch-specific tests - see naming conventions for more info.
        common.inc      - Shared shell helper functions

RUNNING TESTS
    Run all tests:
        cd build
        ctest

    Run component tests:
        ctest -R "^<component>-"
        ctest -L soul                   # All soul tests (by label(expansion planned when integration tests are included, the above suffices for now.)

    Run architecture-specific tests:
        ctest -R "aarch64

    Run specific test:
        ctest -R "^lens-pie$"

    Verbose:
        ctest -V

WRITING TESTS
    1. Create a new .sh file in tests/<component>
    2. Source common.inc
    3. Use helper functions to compile and verify

    Example:
        #!/bin/bash
        . $(dirname $0)/common.inc

        # Create source
        cat > $t/test.c <<EOF
        int main() { return 0; }
        EOF

        # Compile
        compile $t/test.c $t/test

        # Verify (component binary available as $COMPONENT_NAME or $component_name)
        $LENS $t/test | grep "Type:.*EXEC"     # lens
        $SOUL $t/test | grep "expected output" # soul

NAMING CONVENTION
    *.sh  
    arch-arm32-*.sh
    arch-aarch64-*.sh
